==English==
===Etymology===
* From the Greek letter [[delta]] (Δ).

===Noun===
'''delta wing'''
# An [[aircraft]] [[wing]] of [[triangular]] shape. Used in such aircraft as the Avro Vulcan, a British [[w:V bomber|V bomber]] of the 1950s and 1960s.

